The &quot;--perl-regexp&quot; flag to git grep enables perl flavored regexes, which contain explicit word boundary matching. To match only word starts, you could use the following:<p><pre><code>    git grep --perl-regexp &quot;\brout&quot;

</code></pre>
and for just word endings<p><pre><code>    git grep --perl-regexp &quot;outer\b&quot;</code></pre>
